					<p>
						Wuhan university’s media development research center was founded in July 2002. It is China's first cross-regional, cross-industry’s media development research center. Forming the media development research center, aiming at integratingthe media resources of nationwide consider of development, building a platform for the communication of news dissemination theory with practice, promoting our country media’s healthy and rapid development in the new century. The center will be effected according to the national liberal arts scientific research based on the mode of open management and standardized operation. In May, 2004,we passed the ministry of education’s evaluation, succeeding in becoming national key research based on humanities and social science. Center advisor: guangchun Xu (deputy secretary of the communist party's propaganda department), wang Chen (chief editor of the People's Daily), Fang Hanqi (a professor at republic university of China), Ding Ganlin (professor of fudan university), Zhao Yuming (Beijing broadcasting institute professor); The academic committee director: professor luoyicheng; The director of the center: professor zhangjinhai. The Center willregularly published the annual report on China's media development every year.
